= Monospaced Text

Monospaced text is displayed in a fixed-width font, typically used for code.

== Basic Monospaced

This paragraph contains `monospaced text` within it.

This paragraph has ``unconstrained monospaced`` text.

== Monospaced with Code

Use `console.log()` to output to the console.

The function `getElementById()` returns an element.

== Monospaced with Formatting

This paragraph has `*bold monospaced*` text.

This paragraph has `_italic monospaced_` text.

== Monospaced File Paths

The file is located at `/path/to/file.txt`.

Windows path: `C:\Users\Documents\file.txt`.

== Monospaced Commands

Run the command `npm install` to install dependencies.

Use `git status` to check the repository status.

== Monospaced Variables

The variable `$username` contains the user's name.

Set `$config` to configure the application.

== Monospaced in Lists

* Item with `monospaced` text
* Another item with ``monospaced`` text
* Third item

== Monospaced with Links

Visit `https://example.com` for more information.

Check the `README.md` file for details.

